WEBVTT

00:08.443 --> 00:10.010
[school bell rings]
- I can help.

00:10.053 --> 00:12.490
You just need
to have some trust.

00:12.534 --> 00:14.492
Do you read the Bible?

00:14.536 --> 00:15.667
- No.

00:15.711 --> 00:17.887
- [snickers]
Me neither.

00:17.930 --> 00:19.889
My mother used to, though.

00:19.932 --> 00:22.326
When I was down and out, she'd
always quote this same passage.

00:22.370 --> 00:23.632
It goes something like,

00:23.675 --> 00:25.938
"When the righteous
cry for help,

00:25.982 --> 00:28.898
the Lord rescues them
from their trouble."

00:28.941 --> 00:30.334
- I don't get it.

00:30.378 --> 00:32.206
- It means I can't help you,

00:32.249 --> 00:34.077
unless you actually
want my help.

00:34.121 --> 00:36.036
- All you care about is
that little sexy girlfriend

00:36.079 --> 00:37.689
that you always be
around all the time, I--

00:37.733 --> 00:39.343
- Watch yourself, Alex.
- No, you watch yourself!

00:39.387 --> 00:41.432
- Okay, Al.

00:41.476 --> 00:43.217
It's time to go.

00:45.132 --> 00:48.048
[suspenseful music]

00:48.091 --> 00:50.311
♪

00:50.354 --> 00:52.226
You crazy, bro?
I'm trying to help you, man.

00:52.269 --> 00:55.142
- Get off of me!
- Go!

00:55.185 --> 00:57.579
Get out of here.

00:57.622 --> 00:59.233
Now.

01:01.409 --> 01:07.110
♪

01:07.154 --> 01:09.460
[sighs]

01:11.245 --> 01:18.208
♪

01:37.706 --> 01:40.100
[phone beeps]
Hey, uh, it's me.

01:40.143 --> 01:42.972
I'm--I'm on my way home, but...

01:43.015 --> 01:44.278
[distant banging]

01:44.321 --> 01:46.018
[car door chirps]
Yeah, call--

01:46.062 --> 01:47.150
yeah, call the cops,
uh, tell them--

01:47.194 --> 01:49.979
tell them--
tell them--

01:50.022 --> 01:51.154
Please, don't do this, please--
- [grunts]

01:51.198 --> 01:52.416
[tense music]

01:52.460 --> 01:54.636
♪

01:57.029 --> 01:58.292
- This is a small town.

01:58.335 --> 01:59.989
We don't have a lot
of resources,

02:00.032 --> 02:02.122
so I appreciate you guys coming
out and getting involved.

02:02.165 --> 02:03.471
- Of course.

02:03.514 --> 02:04.863
Hi.
- Hi.

02:04.907 --> 02:07.562
- Special Agent Bell.
This is Special Agent Zidan.

02:07.605 --> 02:08.737
- Good luck, Vanessa.

02:08.780 --> 02:10.086
- Thank you.

02:10.130 --> 02:11.827
- [whispers]
Thanks.

02:11.870 --> 02:14.960
- So, Vanessa, can you, um,
just tell us what's going on?

02:15.004 --> 02:17.746
- Yeah, okay.
[sighs]

02:17.789 --> 02:20.879
Well, my boyfriend, Patrick,
never came home last night.

02:20.923 --> 02:22.707
So I called 911,

02:22.751 --> 02:24.448
the police came over,

02:24.492 --> 02:26.711
started asking me questions,
making phone calls.

02:26.755 --> 02:28.322
But then they said
that I should call the FBI--

02:28.365 --> 02:30.454
that you guys are more equipped
to handle things like this.

02:30.498 --> 02:32.369
- Has Patrick ever
not come home before?

02:32.413 --> 02:35.285
- No, he says 8:15,
he means 8:15.

02:35.329 --> 02:39.333
Or 8:10, he's very organized
and disciplined.

02:39.376 --> 02:41.030
- When was the last time
you spoke to him?

02:41.073 --> 02:45.600
- Uh... last night.
About 7:30.

02:45.643 --> 02:48.820
He was in Coney Island walking
around, clearing his head.

02:48.864 --> 02:51.214
He called to say that he was
on his way home, but then he--

02:51.258 --> 02:52.868
he got real nervous,

02:52.911 --> 02:54.609
like--like something
had happened,

02:54.652 --> 02:56.176
or was happening.

02:56.219 --> 02:57.220
- What do you mean?

02:57.264 --> 02:58.917
- He said, "Call the police."

02:58.961 --> 03:00.658
And I was like, "What are you
talking about?

03:00.702 --> 03:02.269
What's going on?"

03:02.312 --> 03:04.967
He didn't respond,
but I heard him say to someone,

03:05.010 --> 03:06.273
"Please don't do this."

03:08.710 --> 03:10.233
- Did you hear anything else?
- I mean, yeah.

03:10.277 --> 03:11.887
I heard some voices,
some yelling,

03:11.930 --> 03:13.454
but then the phone went dead.

03:13.497 --> 03:15.804
- Has anything unusual been
happening in Patrick's life?

03:15.847 --> 03:18.154
Any recent altercations
or arguments?

03:18.198 --> 03:20.983
- Yeah, he got into an argument
yesterday with a student.

03:21.026 --> 03:22.202
Said the kid tried
to punch him.

03:22.245 --> 03:23.725
That's why he went down
to the boardwalk.

03:23.768 --> 03:25.117
He was feeling
really bad about it.

03:25.161 --> 03:27.946
- What's the kid's name?
- I don't know.

03:27.990 --> 03:29.861
I can call the principal
if you want.

03:29.905 --> 03:32.212
- That's okay.
We can take it from here.

03:32.255 --> 03:35.911
Look, if anything else
comes up, please, call me.

03:35.954 --> 03:38.479
♪

03:38.522 --> 03:40.959
- All right, we're looking
for a man named Patrick Miller.

03:41.003 --> 03:43.353
He's an English teacher at West
Harbor High on Long Island.

03:43.397 --> 03:45.050
- He's been missing
since yesterday evening.

03:45.094 --> 03:46.443
His last communication

03:46.487 --> 03:49.098
was with his girlfriend,
Vanessa Gallo, at 7:27 p.m.

03:49.141 --> 03:50.969
During the call, he told her
to call the police,

03:51.013 --> 03:52.841
and his phone went dead
shortly thereafter.

03:52.884 --> 03:54.234
Based on what we know
at the moment,

03:54.277 --> 03:56.410
Mr. Miller appears to be
an upstanding human being.

03:56.453 --> 03:59.500
He was captain
of the Hofstra wrestling team.

03:59.543 --> 04:01.937
He was voted West Harbor High's
Teacher of the Year not once,

04:01.980 --> 04:03.721
not twice, but three times--
- Hey.

04:03.765 --> 04:05.114
- Yeah, tell me.
- I was able to track

04:05.157 --> 04:06.985
the phone call Miller made
to his girlfriend.

04:07.029 --> 04:08.248
- Good, good.
- Pinged off a tower

04:08.291 --> 04:10.119
four blocks from the
Coney Island boardwalk.

04:10.162 --> 04:11.294
- All right, let's do this.

04:11.338 --> 04:13.035
Let's start pulling
surveillance footage

04:13.078 --> 04:15.298
in the vicinity
of the Coney Island Boardwalk.

04:15.342 --> 04:17.257
Put a BOLO out
on Miller's car, and Mike--

04:17.300 --> 04:20.477
Let's get some patrol officers
from the 61st over there.

04:20.521 --> 04:22.305
I'm guessing Mr. Miller's car
isn't too far

04:22.349 --> 04:23.567
from that cell tower.

04:25.482 --> 04:27.223
- A lot of blood
on the pavement.

04:28.964 --> 04:30.531
- On the side of the car too.

04:36.624 --> 04:38.669
- Some on the inside as well.
- Yeah?

04:43.848 --> 04:45.763
- Victim was trying
to get into his car.

04:45.807 --> 04:47.939
Opens the door, gets attacked,

04:47.983 --> 04:50.290
blood starts to fly,
he falls to the ground,

04:50.333 --> 04:52.640
and his head hits the pavement
right about here.

04:52.683 --> 04:55.947
Yeah, and then he, or they,
drag the body that way,

04:55.991 --> 04:57.906
causing these transfer stains.

04:57.949 --> 05:00.778
- Yeah, they were probably
pulling him to a vehicle,

05:00.822 --> 05:03.215
gettin' the hell out of here.

05:03.259 --> 05:05.479
All right, let's get ERT
out here right away.

05:05.522 --> 05:06.958
♪

05:07.002 --> 05:08.438
- I don't know
exactly what happened,

05:08.482 --> 05:09.787
but it was definitely brutal.

05:09.831 --> 05:12.573
The amount of pulling
was significant.

05:12.616 --> 05:15.880
The blood splatter
on the door right here.

05:15.924 --> 05:18.405
Medium velocity impact spatter.

05:18.448 --> 05:21.321
The stains are 2 to 3
millimeters in diameter.

05:21.364 --> 05:22.757
And over here,

05:22.800 --> 05:24.324
we have some castoff.

05:24.367 --> 05:26.761
Looks like an object was swung
in an arc.

05:26.804 --> 05:28.284
- How many times do you think
he was struck?

05:28.328 --> 05:30.068
- Mm, uh...

05:30.112 --> 05:33.594
based on the number
of distinct arcs,

05:33.637 --> 05:35.683
20, maybe more?

05:35.726 --> 05:36.901
- What type of weapon?

05:36.945 --> 05:39.034
- Pipe, maybe...

05:39.077 --> 05:40.905
a baseball bat?

05:40.949 --> 05:42.733
- Any chance
the victim's still alive?

05:42.777 --> 05:45.257
- It's impossible to say for
sure, but it's highly unlikely.

05:45.301 --> 05:47.129
- Okay, so the assailants
attack Miller,

05:47.172 --> 05:49.218
drag him to another vehicle,
and then dump him.

05:49.261 --> 05:52.134
- The question is where.
- And why.

05:52.177 --> 05:53.701
[phone buzzes]
Why would someone do this

05:53.744 --> 05:56.007
to a seemingly decent,
hardworking teacher?

05:56.051 --> 05:56.965
Maggie Bell.

05:58.140 --> 05:59.315
Hey.

06:01.056 --> 06:02.362
Great, great.

06:02.405 --> 06:03.841
Thank you for getting back
to me so quickly.

06:05.669 --> 06:07.454
That was the principal
of West Harbor High.

06:07.497 --> 06:09.151
Alex Williams was the student

06:09.194 --> 06:11.240
who threw a punch
at Patrick Miller.

06:11.283 --> 06:13.503
- Okay, great.
Thank you.

06:13.547 --> 06:16.027
- So we spoke
with your principal yesterday.

06:16.071 --> 06:18.421
Said that you got
into a pretty intense argument

06:18.465 --> 06:20.031
with Mr. Miller.

06:20.075 --> 06:22.164
- So intense that Mr. Miller

06:22.207 --> 06:23.557
filed a report
with the principal.

06:23.600 --> 06:25.428
Said you threw a punch at him.

06:25.472 --> 06:26.516
- Yeah, I did.

06:26.560 --> 06:27.561
- How come?

06:27.604 --> 06:29.737
- Mm. I was mad.

06:29.780 --> 06:31.173
- Mad about what?

06:31.216 --> 06:33.654
- I just wanna graduate,
all right?

06:33.697 --> 06:34.742
- But what?

06:34.785 --> 06:36.396
Mr. Miller said he didn't care?

06:36.439 --> 06:38.006
Said he was gonna fail you
no matter what?

06:38.049 --> 06:39.573
- No, no, he said
the opposite, all right?

06:39.616 --> 06:41.488
He said he was actually trying
to help me get my grade up

06:41.531 --> 06:43.533
so I could graduate.

06:43.577 --> 06:45.535
- So he was trying to help you.

06:47.624 --> 06:49.321
Okay, then why did you
get so upset?

06:49.365 --> 06:50.584
- I don't know!

06:50.627 --> 06:52.194
I guess I was in a bad mood.

06:52.237 --> 06:53.630
I said something
about his girl,

06:53.674 --> 06:56.981
Mr. Miller started tripping,
and he told me to get out.

06:57.025 --> 06:58.330
- Where'd you go after that?

06:58.374 --> 07:00.637
- I went home,
I got something to eat, and...

07:02.683 --> 07:04.511
And then I went to work
at this restaurant.

07:04.554 --> 07:06.164
Vinny's.

07:06.208 --> 07:08.515
- Do you know any students
who don't like Mr. Miller?

07:08.558 --> 07:10.342
Think he's unfair?

07:10.386 --> 07:12.388
- Nah, most of the kids,
they think he's cool.

07:12.432 --> 07:13.955
But I did see him
and this other dude.

07:13.998 --> 07:16.000
A grown-up.
They--

07:16.044 --> 07:17.480
They were going at it
a few days ago

07:17.524 --> 07:19.264
in the school parking lot.

07:19.308 --> 07:20.701
It was pretty nasty too.

07:22.572 --> 07:25.445
[dramatic music]

07:25.488 --> 07:26.881
- Yeah, let's go deeper
into this.

07:26.924 --> 07:29.057
- Hey, the high school kid's
alibi checks out.

07:29.100 --> 07:31.146
- Yeah, he was at Vinny's
from 4:15 to 10:30.

07:31.189 --> 07:32.974
- Okay, what about this
argument in the parking lot?

07:33.017 --> 07:34.845
- Yeah, that checks out too.

07:34.889 --> 07:36.934
Take a look at that.

07:36.978 --> 07:38.153
- All right,
here we go.

07:42.679 --> 07:46.988
♪

07:47.031 --> 07:48.598
Those two
weren't messing around.

07:48.642 --> 07:50.687
- Especially the dude
in the black pickup.

07:50.731 --> 07:52.646
- Yeah, and I think I know why.

07:52.689 --> 07:54.169
That black pickup

07:54.212 --> 07:56.476
belongs to a Max Bailey.

07:56.519 --> 07:58.826
He's married,
he's got one son, age 11.

07:58.869 --> 08:01.002
His wife's name is Vanessa,

08:01.045 --> 08:03.395
as in Vanessa Gallo.

08:03.439 --> 08:04.875
Patrick's girlfriend.

08:14.581 --> 08:15.843
- What?
Max was at the high school?

08:15.886 --> 08:17.758
- He was,
in an argument with Patrick.

08:22.589 --> 08:24.678
- That's really sad.

08:24.721 --> 08:26.680
But I'm not surprised.

08:26.723 --> 08:28.072
- Why do you say that?

08:28.116 --> 08:30.335
- Max isn't taking
the breakup too well.

08:30.379 --> 08:32.555
He's been calling
and texting a lot.

08:32.599 --> 08:34.296
He wanted to get back together,
but I don't.

08:34.339 --> 08:35.906
I keep telling him
that I've moved on,

08:35.950 --> 08:37.081
that I'm dating Patrick.

08:37.125 --> 08:38.474
- Has he ever
said anything specific

08:38.518 --> 08:39.562
about wanting to hurt Patrick?

08:39.606 --> 08:41.433
- [sighs]
No.

08:41.477 --> 08:44.219
But a few days ago,

08:44.262 --> 08:46.264
I told him Patrick and I
were going to get married

08:46.308 --> 08:48.092
after the divorce
was finalized.

08:48.136 --> 08:49.398
And he got really upset.

08:49.441 --> 08:50.573
He said he still loved me,

08:50.617 --> 08:53.445
that he deserved
another chance.

08:53.489 --> 08:55.230
Then he called me a whore,

08:55.273 --> 08:57.928
threw a beer bottle,
and stormed out.

08:59.974 --> 09:01.410
[pensive music]
[loud banging]

09:01.453 --> 09:04.631
- Max Bailey!
FBI!

09:04.674 --> 09:06.154
- I'll walk around back.

09:06.197 --> 09:10.071
[muffled rap music playing]

09:10.114 --> 09:12.726
- ♪ Polo hangin',
double-X white tee ♪

09:12.769 --> 09:15.598
♪ Might be singing,
nah, I'm a rapper ♪

09:15.642 --> 09:18.601
♪ Clap you, after the bread,
this the final chapter ♪

09:18.645 --> 09:19.559
♪ You want a raise

09:19.602 --> 09:20.603
[music stops]

09:20.647 --> 09:21.604
- Mr. Bailey!
[gun clicks]

09:21.648 --> 09:23.650
- Don't move.

09:23.693 --> 09:25.782
- Sir.

09:25.826 --> 09:29.090
I'm going to turn around
nice and slow.

09:29.133 --> 09:31.222
- The hell you doing here?
Snooping around?

09:34.399 --> 09:36.880
- Mr. Bailey.
I'm with the FBI.

09:36.924 --> 09:38.403
- So am I.

09:38.447 --> 09:41.058
Drop the weapon now,
or I will shoot you.

09:41.102 --> 09:45.323
- We just want to ask you
some questions, Max, okay?

09:45.367 --> 09:48.196
Do yourself a favor,
and put the weapon down.

09:48.239 --> 09:49.371
Now.

09:50.807 --> 09:53.767
[dramatic music]

09:53.810 --> 09:56.552
♪

09:56.596 --> 09:58.119
- Look.

09:58.162 --> 10:00.643
Look, man, I'm sorry, I-I
thought you were someone else.

10:00.687 --> 10:02.123
All right?
I owe this guy money.

10:02.166 --> 10:04.168
He said he was sending someone
over to collect, all right?

10:04.212 --> 10:05.605
I had no clue you were FBI.

10:05.648 --> 10:07.345
- Perfectly understandable,
Max.

10:07.389 --> 10:10.218
Debt collectors make
rational people nervous.

10:10.261 --> 10:13.003
In fact, we might even overlook
what just happened.

10:13.047 --> 10:17.442
But you're gonna need to answer
some questions first.

10:17.486 --> 10:19.401
- What do you mean
Patrick Miller's gone missing?

10:19.444 --> 10:21.185
- We mean no one's seen him

10:21.229 --> 10:23.884
or talked to him
for the past 19 hours.

10:23.927 --> 10:25.363
- So?

10:25.407 --> 10:27.801
- So we found a lot of blood
near his car--his blood.

10:27.844 --> 10:30.368
And we're pretty sure he's not
sipping margaritas in Cabo

10:30.412 --> 10:31.631
right now.
- Well, maybe not,

10:31.674 --> 10:33.328
but that's got
nothing to do with me.

10:33.371 --> 10:34.721
I got no idea where he is.

10:34.764 --> 10:37.811
- So this has nothing to do
with him dating Vanessa?

10:37.854 --> 10:40.640
Or that little argument the two
of you got into a few days ago

10:40.683 --> 10:43.207
at West Harbor High School?
- No, nothing.

10:43.251 --> 10:45.688
- Nothing, okay, so what were
you two chatting about?

10:45.732 --> 10:47.124
- This guy Miller's bad news.

10:47.168 --> 10:49.823
And I don't want him
near my wife or my family.

10:49.866 --> 10:52.303
- Why?
- He's a pedophile.

10:52.347 --> 10:54.218
[stark music]

10:54.262 --> 10:55.437
- Do you have proof of this?

10:55.480 --> 10:57.047
- He's dating
one of his students.

10:57.091 --> 10:58.658
- You need to be
more specific, pal.

10:58.701 --> 11:00.660
- All right, look.

11:00.703 --> 11:03.706
I'm not proud of this,
but I started following him.

11:03.750 --> 11:05.273
And the other day,

11:05.316 --> 11:06.753
I saw him on some street corner
with a young girl.

11:06.796 --> 11:09.364
I don't know, 16, 17.

11:09.407 --> 11:11.192
And they were talking
real close and personal.

11:11.235 --> 11:13.673
So I jumped out of my car
and confronted him.

11:13.716 --> 11:14.978
He totally freaked out.

11:15.022 --> 11:16.371
Told the girl to run away,

11:16.414 --> 11:18.373
begged me to keep
my mouth shut.

11:18.416 --> 11:19.548
He offered me cash too.

11:19.591 --> 11:21.332
- Well, what did you say?

11:21.376 --> 11:23.117
- "Stay away from Vanessa,
or I'll tell the world

11:23.160 --> 11:24.945
you're screwing
one of your students."

11:29.036 --> 11:30.994
- All, right, Trey,
appreciate it--take care of it?

11:31.038 --> 11:32.604
- Hey.
- Hey.

11:32.648 --> 11:34.389
- I think Max Bailey
might be telling the truth.

11:34.432 --> 11:36.086
- Yeah, about what?
- Everything.

11:36.130 --> 11:38.088
- Agents searched his car,
apartment, office.

11:38.132 --> 11:40.090
Haven't found anything
connecting him to the attack.

11:40.134 --> 11:41.613
- And that story
about the young girl?

11:41.657 --> 11:43.311
That appears to be true
as well.

11:43.354 --> 11:45.835
He told us where he saw Miller
and this young girl talking,

11:45.879 --> 11:48.708
so we searched the neighborhood
for surveillance video,

11:48.751 --> 11:50.144
and we found this.

11:53.408 --> 11:54.365
- Hmm.

11:56.759 --> 11:58.761
All right, let's track down
the girl in this video.

11:58.805 --> 12:00.545
She could be the reason
Miller was attacked.

12:00.589 --> 12:03.548
Assailant could be an angry
father, brother, boyfriend.

12:03.592 --> 12:05.159
All right, good,
you guys want to head out

12:05.202 --> 12:06.595
to Miller's apartment,
see what you can find?

12:06.638 --> 12:08.379
I'll call Maggie and OA,
send them to the high school.

12:08.423 --> 12:09.816
- Will do.

12:09.859 --> 12:11.382
- Okay, well, do you
recognize her by any chance?

12:11.426 --> 12:14.646
- No, I have no idea.
I can't really see her face.

12:14.690 --> 12:16.083
But this has to be a mistake.

12:16.126 --> 12:17.867
There's no way Patrick Miller

12:17.911 --> 12:19.782
is romantically involved
with a student.

12:19.826 --> 12:22.089
I just can't see it.

12:22.132 --> 12:23.264
His record is impeccable.

12:23.307 --> 12:24.439
- Maybe.

12:24.482 --> 12:26.006
I'd like to check it out
myself anyway.

12:26.049 --> 12:28.791
- Well, like I said before,
Patrick likes to make deep,

12:28.835 --> 12:31.576
meaningful connections
with his students.

12:31.620 --> 12:35.624
This Bailey fella probably just
misinterpreted what he saw.

12:35.667 --> 12:38.105
- We understand you have a high
level of respect for him,

12:38.148 --> 12:39.889
but could you please
let us do our job?

12:41.891 --> 12:42.849
Thank you.

12:46.374 --> 12:47.767
Locked?
- Yup.

12:49.812 --> 12:52.119
- Okay, let me see
if I can still do this.

12:53.598 --> 12:56.514
[suspenseful music]

12:56.558 --> 13:00.431
♪

13:00.475 --> 13:01.737
- Okay.

13:05.088 --> 13:12.052
♪

13:14.837 --> 13:16.665
I think I got something.

13:16.708 --> 13:18.014
"I don't know what I'd do
without you.

13:18.058 --> 13:19.363
"I'll meet you
anywhere, anytime

13:19.407 --> 13:21.583
as long as no one finds out.
J."

13:21.626 --> 13:24.368
- Okay, well, it is definitely
deep and meaningful,

13:24.412 --> 13:25.674
but not in a good way.

13:25.717 --> 13:28.242
- We should get this
to the lab right away.

13:28.285 --> 13:31.332
- Been 21 hours and Patrick
Miller is still missing.

13:31.375 --> 13:33.856
The angry, gun-toting,
soon-to-be ex-husband

13:33.900 --> 13:37.686
of Miller's gal pal has just
officially been alibi'd out.

13:37.729 --> 13:40.558
He was at his son's soccer game
until 5:39 p.m., and then

13:40.602 --> 13:42.386
he went to dinner with the team
at a local pizza joint.

13:42.430 --> 13:44.040
He was there until...

13:44.084 --> 13:46.826
7:45 p.m.

13:46.869 --> 13:48.218
For the record,

13:48.262 --> 13:49.872
he ordered a large pepperoni
and mushroom pie,

13:49.916 --> 13:51.569
a chef's salad,
and two Diet Cokes.

13:51.613 --> 13:52.875
But more importantly,

13:52.919 --> 13:54.485
that means our only lead
is a young brunette

13:54.529 --> 13:55.878
we believe attends
West Harbor High.

13:55.922 --> 13:58.011
Problem is we don't know
anything about her,

13:58.054 --> 14:01.362
or how--or if--she's actually
connected to any of this.

14:01.405 --> 14:02.754
- So--
- Jubal.

14:02.798 --> 14:05.061
- Yes, Elise, please tell me
you have something.

14:05.105 --> 14:07.020
- We pulled a print from
the from the note Maggie found

14:07.063 --> 14:09.022
in Miller's office,
got a hit too.

14:09.065 --> 14:10.458
Jessica Sanchez.

14:10.501 --> 14:12.373
Senior at West Harbor
High School.

14:12.416 --> 14:15.202
Came to the U.S. two years ago
from Tampico, Mexico,

14:15.245 --> 14:16.681
was granted temporary asylum,

14:16.725 --> 14:18.770
and is living with her aunt
in Mineola.

14:18.814 --> 14:20.207
- All right.
That's something.

14:20.250 --> 14:22.209
Send Maggie and OA
the address right away.

14:25.560 --> 14:28.171
- These people are FBI.
They wanna talk to you, Jess.

14:28.215 --> 14:29.607
Said it was important.

14:29.651 --> 14:31.566
I gotta go to work, so.
- Yeah, that's okay.

14:31.609 --> 14:33.089
Like I said, we just wanna
talk to Jess--

14:33.133 --> 14:34.090
- She in trouble?
- No.

14:34.134 --> 14:35.091
- Do I need a lawyer?
- No.

14:35.135 --> 14:36.092
She's not in trouble, ma'am.

14:39.182 --> 14:41.097
- Jessica, we just wanna
ask you a couple questions

14:41.141 --> 14:43.708
about your English teacher,
Patrick Miller.

14:43.752 --> 14:45.362
Do you two spend a lot
of time together?

14:45.406 --> 14:47.016
- What does that mean?
- We're just trying

14:47.060 --> 14:48.931
to understand the nature
of your relationship.

14:48.975 --> 14:51.107
Do you two see each other
outside of the classroom?

14:51.151 --> 14:52.935
- Yeah.

14:52.979 --> 14:55.024
But I don't want to talk
about any of that.

15:00.987 --> 15:02.902
- Look, Jessica, um,

15:02.945 --> 15:04.904
if your relationship
is in any way romantic,

15:04.947 --> 15:07.384
or you're having sex,

15:07.428 --> 15:09.256
it's not your fault.

15:09.299 --> 15:10.910
- Sex?
What are you talking about?

15:10.953 --> 15:12.999
Mr. Miller was my teacher.

15:13.042 --> 15:15.610
He was my friend.
He was trying to save my life.

15:17.046 --> 15:19.222
- What do you mean?

15:19.266 --> 15:20.615
- He was trying
to help get me out.

15:20.658 --> 15:22.660
- I'm sorry.
Get you out of what?

15:24.097 --> 15:25.272
- Gang life.

15:27.578 --> 15:29.841
I've been with the DT 15s
since I was 13,

15:29.885 --> 15:32.540
but I can't take it anymore,
I just--

15:32.583 --> 15:35.412
I wanna live a normal life,
I wanna do normal things.

15:35.456 --> 15:39.068
And Mr. Miller was gonna
help me do all of that, but...

15:39.112 --> 15:41.288
now he's dead.

15:41.331 --> 15:44.204
- Dead?
You know that for sure?

15:44.247 --> 15:46.249
- Yeah.

15:46.293 --> 15:48.469
Some people told me.

15:48.512 --> 15:50.036
- Do you know
where his body is?

15:53.474 --> 15:56.172
[dog panting]

15:57.913 --> 16:00.046
[police radio chatter]

16:00.089 --> 16:03.005
[whimpers, barks]

16:03.049 --> 16:04.964
- We got something.

16:05.007 --> 16:06.791
- Wait, Jessica, hold on.
Just wait.

16:10.795 --> 16:12.275
- We got a body.

16:12.319 --> 16:14.016
- It's him.
- [gasps]

16:14.060 --> 16:17.150
- Okay, okay, come on.
Let's go over here.

16:17.193 --> 16:18.978
- It's my fault,
this whole thing.

16:19.021 --> 16:20.675
- But why do you think
this is your fault?

16:20.718 --> 16:22.111
- Some of the guys
in the gang--

16:22.155 --> 16:24.418
they heard Mr. Miller talking
about trying to help me.

16:24.461 --> 16:25.941
- You think that's why
they killed him?

16:25.985 --> 16:29.814
- Yes, but it's my fault
because I went to him.

16:29.858 --> 16:31.686
- Wait, the gang doesn't know
that you want out?

16:31.729 --> 16:34.036
- No, because if they did,

16:34.080 --> 16:36.517
I'd be right there on the
ground next to Mr. Miller.

16:36.560 --> 16:38.258
- Okay, let's get back
in the car.

16:46.440 --> 16:48.007
- Cause of death
was blunt force trauma.

16:48.050 --> 16:50.487
Multiple contusions along
the cervical spine and abdomen.

16:50.531 --> 16:53.186
Multiple perimortem
cranial fractures.

16:53.229 --> 16:55.753
In plain English, he was beaten
to death by a heavy object.

16:55.797 --> 16:57.755
I'm guessing a baseball bat.

16:57.799 --> 17:00.236
- Hmm, multiple assailants?
- Looks that way.

17:00.280 --> 17:01.585
There's also
several lacerations

17:01.629 --> 17:03.239
along the groin and thigh area.

17:03.283 --> 17:04.632
- So someone was slashing him

17:04.675 --> 17:07.678
while the others
were beating him?

17:07.722 --> 17:08.940
Any defensive wounds?

17:08.984 --> 17:10.551
- No, it wasn't much
of a fight.

17:10.594 --> 17:12.727
- Mm, well... bats and machetes

17:12.770 --> 17:14.468
have a tendency
to make fights less fair.

17:14.511 --> 17:16.905
- But I did find
some saliva on the body.

17:16.948 --> 17:17.949
Sent it off to the lab.

17:17.993 --> 17:20.517
- Great.
Maybe put a rush on that?

17:22.954 --> 17:25.044
[door buzzes]

17:25.087 --> 17:28.264
Okay, Jessica, we're gonna
need you to tell us everything.

17:28.308 --> 17:31.746
Start from the beginning, okay?
What you saw, what you heard.

17:31.789 --> 17:32.747
Here, have a seat.

17:37.186 --> 17:39.319
- Okay, well,

17:39.362 --> 17:42.191
I wasn't there,
so I didn't see anything.

17:42.235 --> 17:44.715
And I don't know for sure
who actually killed him.

17:44.759 --> 17:47.805
I just heard people talking.
That's all.

17:47.849 --> 17:49.590
- You're gonna have
to help us out.

17:49.633 --> 17:51.200
You just woke up one day
and said,

17:51.244 --> 17:52.549
"I don't wanna be in a gang?"

17:52.593 --> 17:54.682
- No.

17:54.725 --> 17:58.686
I woke up every day
of my life saying that.

17:58.729 --> 18:02.472
In my town, Tampico,
everyone I know is DT 15.

18:02.516 --> 18:04.735
My brothers, uncle.

18:04.779 --> 18:07.608
And they made me join.
And I hated it.

18:07.651 --> 18:08.783
It just made me
nervous and sad,

18:08.826 --> 18:10.959
and I cried all the time.

18:11.002 --> 18:12.526
And I just--
I had to get out of there.

18:12.569 --> 18:15.224
So I got a note from a doctor.

18:15.268 --> 18:17.226
And I told everyone
that I was really sick

18:17.270 --> 18:18.488
and that I needed to go
to New York

18:18.532 --> 18:22.405
to go to a special hospital
or I'd die.

18:22.449 --> 18:25.887
And then they found me in
school and made me come back.

18:25.930 --> 18:28.107
- Made you?

18:28.150 --> 18:30.152
- If I didn't, they'd kill me.

18:30.196 --> 18:31.719
This gang thing is for life.

18:31.762 --> 18:35.070
The only way out is a coffin.

18:35.114 --> 18:38.160
- Jessica, I'm gonna get you
out of this gang.

18:38.204 --> 18:40.336
[solemn music]

18:40.380 --> 18:43.252
But will you help us find the
people who killed Mr. Miller?

18:43.296 --> 18:44.601
♪

18:44.645 --> 18:46.734
- I'll do anything you want.

18:46.777 --> 18:48.953
Anything, I just...

18:48.997 --> 18:51.913
want to be free.

18:51.956 --> 18:54.698
- Okay.

18:54.742 --> 18:56.309
Can you tell us
about your past?

18:56.352 --> 18:57.962
About the crimes
that you've committed?

18:58.006 --> 19:00.443
Because that's the only way
that we can really help you.

19:00.487 --> 19:04.621
- Okay.
I'll tell you everything.

19:04.665 --> 19:06.449
Sometimes, we steal stuff.

19:06.493 --> 19:09.235
You know, food, liquor.

19:09.278 --> 19:11.150
And we ask
for protection money

19:11.193 --> 19:12.847
from stores and businesses.

19:12.890 --> 19:14.370
And if they say no,

19:14.414 --> 19:16.807
we break their windows
or slash their tires.

19:16.851 --> 19:19.070
And if they keep saying no,

19:19.114 --> 19:21.595
that's when the boys
get violent.

19:21.638 --> 19:23.771
You know,
beat them up with bats.

19:23.814 --> 19:27.253
But I've never
actually done that, so.

19:27.296 --> 19:29.907
- Thank you.

19:29.951 --> 19:31.866
I appreciate your honesty.

19:31.909 --> 19:33.389
- Yeah.

19:33.433 --> 19:35.826
- We are gonna run this
by our boss.

19:39.874 --> 19:42.181
- Okay, but there's one more
thing I should tell you.

19:42.224 --> 19:43.399
- Okay.

19:45.445 --> 19:48.448
- When I was 14,
I killed someone.

19:50.319 --> 19:55.846
♪

19:55.890 --> 19:58.109
- Can you tell us
what happened?

19:58.153 --> 19:59.937
- There was this guy

19:59.981 --> 20:01.635
named Ernesto.

20:01.678 --> 20:04.072
They thought he was stealing
from the gang.

20:04.115 --> 20:05.726
And so,

20:05.769 --> 20:08.119
they tied him up

20:08.163 --> 20:10.121
around a tree.

20:10.165 --> 20:14.648
The leader, Miguel,
he gave me a machete

20:14.691 --> 20:17.955
and he told me
to slit his throat.

20:17.999 --> 20:20.784
- He looked at me, he said,

20:20.828 --> 20:23.222
"If you don't do it,
we gotta kill you."

20:23.265 --> 20:26.442
And then he looked
to my uncle, pulled out a gun,

20:26.486 --> 20:29.358
and pointed it at my head.

20:29.402 --> 20:30.881
He said,

20:30.925 --> 20:33.580
"It's just the way it is, Jess.

20:33.623 --> 20:36.844
Just do what you gotta do.

20:36.887 --> 20:40.021
Please."

20:40.064 --> 20:43.503
And so I did it.

20:43.546 --> 20:46.375
I slit his throat.

20:52.773 --> 20:59.475
♪

21:08.919 --> 21:10.269
- [sighs]

21:12.706 --> 21:15.274
I will talk to the people
in our Mexico City office.

21:15.317 --> 21:17.232
See if I can confirm her story.

21:17.276 --> 21:20.104
Then call
the U.S. Attorney's office

21:20.148 --> 21:22.411
and get the ball rolling on the
Witness Protection Program.

21:22.455 --> 21:27.416
- Okay, great.
Thank you.

21:27.460 --> 21:29.592
- She is gonna have to deliver
something pretty good.

21:29.636 --> 21:31.768
The U.S. Attorney's office
doesn't just hand out

21:31.812 --> 21:33.292
free passes.
- Mm-hmm.

21:33.335 --> 21:35.511
- Especially when the person
confesses to murder.

21:35.555 --> 21:37.383
- No.

21:40.255 --> 21:41.517
- I know.

21:41.561 --> 21:43.650
The circumstances are unique.
I get it.

21:43.693 --> 21:45.826
But in the eyes of the law,
it's a murder.

21:48.307 --> 21:49.960
Look, obviously,
I'm rooting for this kid.

21:50.004 --> 21:52.267
I just wanna make sure
that she's telling the truth.

21:52.311 --> 21:54.008
- She is.

21:54.051 --> 21:57.011
You can see it in her eyes.
I mean, she's just a kid, OA.

21:57.054 --> 21:58.839
Okay, a decent, innocent kid

21:58.882 --> 22:00.493
who was born
into a horrible situation.

22:00.536 --> 22:02.973
- I understand.
Trust me.

22:03.017 --> 22:05.367
But not every kid born
into crap ends up in a gang

22:05.411 --> 22:07.064
or killing someone.

22:07.108 --> 22:10.198
- Well, she had no choice.
- There is always a choice.

22:10.241 --> 22:12.331
- She was 14 years old, OA.

22:12.374 --> 22:15.943
Okay, her uncle had a gun
to her head.

22:15.986 --> 22:18.815
Oh, what would you do, huh?
Given the same choice.

22:18.859 --> 22:20.121
Are you gonna take the bullet?

22:20.164 --> 22:21.514
Or are you gonna slit
the guy's throat?

22:21.557 --> 22:23.385
- I'd like to think
that I would take the bullet.

22:23.429 --> 22:25.344
- Yeah, I'd love to think
the same thing.

22:25.387 --> 22:26.562
Pretty easy
to be a hero, though,

22:26.606 --> 22:28.347
when no one is pointing
a gun at you.

22:30.044 --> 22:32.655
♪

22:32.699 --> 22:34.962
We've got a camera
in this necklace.

22:35.005 --> 22:37.965
So just put that on
and you're all set.

22:38.008 --> 22:40.402
Most importantly, be careful.

22:40.446 --> 22:41.969
Don't push for information.

22:42.012 --> 22:45.146
Let your friends
do all the talking.

22:45.189 --> 22:47.496
Hopefully, someone will admit
to the murder.

22:47.540 --> 22:49.368
- Yeah, I get it.
I know how to play these dudes.

22:49.411 --> 22:51.326
- Good news.

22:51.370 --> 22:54.460
We got a hit on the saliva.
Someone named Marco Gomez.

22:54.503 --> 22:56.766
- You know him?

22:56.810 --> 22:59.421
- Yeah.
He's the leader of our set.

22:59.465 --> 23:00.901
- Okay.

23:00.944 --> 23:04.252
If possible, try to focus
your attention on him.

23:04.295 --> 23:05.296
- Yeah.

23:05.340 --> 23:06.863
The fact that his saliva,
his spit,

23:06.907 --> 23:08.865
was on Mr. Miller's body
means that he was there,

23:08.909 --> 23:10.389
and most likely
part of the murder.

23:10.432 --> 23:12.434
- That alone is not enough
to arrest him.

23:12.478 --> 23:14.523
We need him to say
something incriminating.

23:17.613 --> 23:24.707
♪

23:24.751 --> 23:27.188
- Jessica's entering
the arcade now.

23:27.231 --> 23:28.842
- Copy that.

23:32.889 --> 23:35.849
[beeping and pinging]

23:35.892 --> 23:37.894
♪

23:37.938 --> 23:40.244
- Whoo!

23:40.288 --> 23:42.377
♪

23:42.421 --> 23:43.552
- Told you.
- Told me.

23:43.596 --> 23:44.727
- You owe me.

23:44.771 --> 23:48.905
♪

23:48.949 --> 23:50.820
- What's going on?

23:50.864 --> 23:52.561
- Lot of things, J.

23:52.605 --> 23:54.694
But before we go any further,

23:54.737 --> 23:57.566
I need to know
if you're down with us.

23:57.610 --> 23:59.089
- What are you talking about?

24:01.962 --> 24:03.485
This got something to do
with that teacher?

24:03.529 --> 24:04.921
- Who?
- Miller.

24:04.965 --> 24:06.314
The teacher at my school.

24:06.357 --> 24:08.795
- Come on, Jessica.
Don't push.

24:08.838 --> 24:10.536
- I don't know nothing
about that.

24:10.579 --> 24:12.451
- He ain't talking about that.
- Fine, you know that

24:12.494 --> 24:14.888
you guys started all this crap
asking me if I'm down.

24:14.931 --> 24:16.803
Hell, I've been down
longer than any of y'all.

24:16.846 --> 24:19.501
So don't come at me like that.

24:19.545 --> 24:21.677
- Okay, this isn't going well.

24:23.810 --> 24:29.337
♪

24:29.380 --> 24:33.254
- She's right, y'all.
Homey's been legit since 13.

24:33.297 --> 24:36.518
She even did some real work
back in Mexico too.

24:36.562 --> 24:38.215
Yeah, I heard about that.

24:40.217 --> 24:41.523
- So we good then?

24:41.567 --> 24:42.742
- Yeah.

24:44.395 --> 24:45.919
We good.

24:45.962 --> 24:47.486
- Okay.

24:47.529 --> 24:48.965
- In fact,

24:49.009 --> 24:51.315
we're having a party
later on today.

24:51.359 --> 24:54.449
I want you to invite
your friend, Kayla.

24:56.320 --> 24:57.452
Is there a problem with that?

24:58.888 --> 25:00.673
- [grunts]
No.

25:02.065 --> 25:03.589
No problem.

25:05.416 --> 25:06.592
- Good.

25:10.117 --> 25:12.554
[person shouts in distance]

25:12.598 --> 25:19.213
♪

25:19.256 --> 25:21.084
- You okay?
- Not really.

25:21.128 --> 25:23.260
- Why?
What happened?

25:23.304 --> 25:25.436
- Gomez wants me to invite my
best friend, Kayla, to a party.

25:25.480 --> 25:28.048
- Why is that bad?

25:28.091 --> 25:32.356
- Inviting someone to a party
is code for killing.

25:32.400 --> 25:36.535
Gomez wants me
to kill Kayla later today.

25:36.578 --> 25:39.929
If I don't, he'll kill me.

25:48.590 --> 25:50.070
- They want Jessica
to kill her friend today?

25:50.113 --> 25:51.550
- Yeah, so do we pull her?

25:51.593 --> 25:52.855
Seems risky
to keep her in play.

25:52.899 --> 25:54.291
- Yeah, but it might be
riskier not to.

25:54.335 --> 25:55.858
If we pull her,
we're gonna blow her cover.

25:55.902 --> 25:56.946
And the gang will think that

25:56.990 --> 25:58.382
she got nervous
and started talking.

25:58.426 --> 25:59.775
I mean, even worse,

25:59.819 --> 26:01.603
we're pulling out the rug
from underneath her.

26:01.647 --> 26:03.083
She'll have nothing to trade.

26:03.126 --> 26:04.432
We won't be able to get her
into WITSEC.

26:04.475 --> 26:06.129
- Yeah, so let's do the course.

26:06.173 --> 26:10.133
- Okay, what about
the target, Kayla?

26:10.177 --> 26:12.614
- Have Scola and Kristen pick
her up, get her off the street.

26:12.658 --> 26:14.573
As far as Jessica's concerned,
tell her

26:14.616 --> 26:16.357
it's business as usual.

26:16.400 --> 26:19.403
Make the calls, send the texts,
whatever the gang wants.

26:19.447 --> 26:21.492
Gomez needs to believe that
she's willing to kill Kayla.

26:23.538 --> 26:25.496
[knocking on door]
- FBI, open up.

26:28.412 --> 26:30.284
[dog barking in distance]

26:32.634 --> 26:34.157
- What happened?
What's going on?

26:34.201 --> 26:35.637
- Ma'am, we need
to speak with Kayla.

26:35.681 --> 26:37.900
- She's not here, why?
She's my daughter.

26:37.944 --> 26:40.816
- Do you know where she is?
Okay, can you call her, please?

26:42.557 --> 26:44.428
- Look, ma'am, we're just
trying to keep her safe.

26:44.472 --> 26:46.213
Can you call her?

26:46.256 --> 26:48.215
- She don't have
a regular phone.

26:48.258 --> 26:49.651
She buys the kind
at the bodega--

26:49.695 --> 26:51.087
the ones you pay for up front.

26:51.131 --> 26:53.263
She bought one today.
Just threw out the box.

26:53.307 --> 26:56.223
- Is it still in the trash?

26:56.266 --> 26:57.877
You mind if I grab it?
Okay.

27:03.622 --> 27:05.798
Jubal, yeah,
we don't have eyes on Kayla,

27:05.841 --> 27:08.627
but I do have the IMEI number
off her burner phone.

27:08.670 --> 27:13.370
Yeah, it is Z234-KT221.

27:13.414 --> 27:14.720
Okay, let me know.

27:14.763 --> 27:16.591
- Searched the house.
Nothing too interesting.

27:16.635 --> 27:18.506
So let's get back out there.
See if we can track her down.

27:18.549 --> 27:19.986
- Okay.

27:20.029 --> 27:22.249
Um, ma'am?

27:22.292 --> 27:25.121
If you hear from Kayla,
or you find out where she is,

27:25.165 --> 27:29.299
call me, but please don't
tell her we were here, okay?

27:29.343 --> 27:31.519
- Don't tell her--you want me
to lie to my own daughter?

27:31.562 --> 27:35.131
- As confusing and crazy
as that sounds, yes, we do.

27:35.175 --> 27:36.611
- But why?

27:36.655 --> 27:39.788
- Because if you don't,
Kayla will be killed.

27:39.832 --> 27:41.660
It's as simple as that.

27:44.880 --> 27:50.625
♪

27:50.669 --> 27:53.236
- If we find Kayla, you know,
we're gonna grab her

27:53.280 --> 27:54.890
and we're gonna hold her
on some made-up charge

27:54.934 --> 27:56.283
until this whole thing
blows over.

27:56.326 --> 27:58.067
But we're never
gonna mention your name,

27:58.111 --> 27:59.895
and we won't blow your cover.
- Okay, good.

27:59.939 --> 28:01.201
- So look,
you're never actually

28:01.244 --> 28:02.419
gonna come face-to-face
with Kayla--

28:02.463 --> 28:03.899
we'd never put you
in that position,

28:03.943 --> 28:05.727
and we'd never expose Kayla
to that type of risk.

28:05.771 --> 28:07.598
- So, what I want you to do

28:07.642 --> 28:09.688
is just go in there
and play along.

28:09.731 --> 28:11.777
Hopefully Gomez and the others
will just start bragging

28:11.820 --> 28:14.127
about what they did to Miller.
- I can do that.

28:14.170 --> 28:16.346
As long as you promise
to help me when this is over

28:16.390 --> 28:19.741
'cause I'm all alone,
I got nowhere to go.

28:19.785 --> 28:21.656
- You have my word.

28:21.700 --> 28:25.573
- Yeah, well, how do I know
if your word is any good?

28:30.099 --> 28:34.321
- Jessica, do I seem like
someone whose word isn't good?

28:34.364 --> 28:36.889
- No.

28:36.932 --> 28:39.805
You're real.
I can see it.

28:39.848 --> 28:42.633
I didn't mean no disrespect.
I just had to make sure.

28:42.677 --> 28:45.811
- That's okay.
Look.

28:45.854 --> 28:47.421
We got you.

28:50.032 --> 28:52.992
[solemn music]

28:53.035 --> 28:56.386
♪

28:56.430 --> 28:58.606
- [sighs]
Is she ready?

28:58.649 --> 29:00.434
- Yeah.

29:00.477 --> 29:03.393
[suspenseful music]

29:08.790 --> 29:10.531
- Okay, we're up.

29:10.574 --> 29:12.228
[computer beeps]

29:12.272 --> 29:19.148
♪

29:22.543 --> 29:24.632
- You owe me
a hundred bucks, bro.

29:24.675 --> 29:26.112
- Whoa-ho!
- Okay, okay.

29:26.155 --> 29:28.331
- These fools were betting
that you wouldn't show, Jess.

29:28.375 --> 29:31.117
But I knew better.
'Cause I believe in you.

29:31.160 --> 29:34.468
- I ain't here to prove myself
to you or no one else.

29:34.511 --> 29:36.339
I'm here to do work.

29:36.383 --> 29:37.819
For the gang.

29:37.863 --> 29:39.429
- That's right.

29:39.473 --> 29:40.779
It ain't about me.

29:40.822 --> 29:42.084
It's about us.

29:42.128 --> 29:44.260
DT 15 por vida.

29:44.304 --> 29:46.219
[gang members speak Spanish]

29:46.262 --> 29:48.830
♪

29:48.874 --> 29:51.964
- Jubal, we got a car
pulling up to the warehouse.

29:52.007 --> 29:53.182
- Is it Kayla?

29:53.226 --> 29:54.314
- Can't tell yet.

29:54.357 --> 29:56.316
- If it is,
intercept her immediately.

29:56.359 --> 29:57.317
- Copy that.

29:59.145 --> 30:04.411
♪

30:04.454 --> 30:05.629
- Jeez.

30:05.673 --> 30:06.979
- That's a hell of a knife.
- Yep.

30:07.022 --> 30:08.502
Be ready, guys.

30:08.545 --> 30:10.591
We're gonna roll
on the first sign of trouble.

30:10.634 --> 30:12.767
- Jubal, the driver is a male
Hispanic with a machete.

30:12.811 --> 30:13.986
No sign of Kayla yet.

30:14.029 --> 30:15.509
- Copy that, Kristen and Scola

30:15.552 --> 30:17.990
are in the vicinity trying
to locate her--so far, no luck.

30:18.033 --> 30:19.992
But we just got her number.
We're running it now.

30:20.035 --> 30:21.341
We'll keep you posted.

30:21.384 --> 30:23.038
- So, Jess,

30:23.082 --> 30:25.127
I'll be straight up with you.

30:25.171 --> 30:27.173
I like you,

30:27.216 --> 30:28.739
but I've been getting nervous.

30:28.783 --> 30:32.004
So you agreeing to do this
is important.

30:32.047 --> 30:33.744
♪

30:33.788 --> 30:35.398
- I just got a hit
on Kayla's phone--

30:35.442 --> 30:36.878
pinged off a tower 100 yards

30:36.922 --> 30:38.184
from the warehouse
they're in right now.

30:38.227 --> 30:39.620
- What?
- Go.

30:39.663 --> 30:41.013
- Maggie, Kayla is in
the immediate vicinity.

30:41.056 --> 30:42.362
Get eyes on her right away.

30:42.405 --> 30:43.972
If you can't find her
in the next two minutes,

30:44.016 --> 30:46.583
hit that warehouse.

30:46.627 --> 30:49.238
- So, why Kayla?
What'd she do?

30:49.282 --> 30:51.153
- She ain't been loyal.

30:51.197 --> 30:54.113
Spending too much time
with the Bloods and the MS-13.

30:54.156 --> 30:55.897
Makes me nervous.

30:55.941 --> 30:58.334
Shows lack of commitment.

30:58.378 --> 30:59.770
- I understand.

30:59.814 --> 31:01.555
- So you gotta send a message.

31:01.598 --> 31:03.992
And it's gotta be
cold-blooded and messy.

31:07.735 --> 31:09.432
Want you to use this.

31:13.219 --> 31:15.569
And slit that bitch's throat.

31:17.963 --> 31:19.834
♪

31:19.878 --> 31:21.749
- Okay.

31:21.792 --> 31:24.491
Just tell me where she is,
and I'll go find her.

31:24.534 --> 31:26.232
- You don't need
to find her ass, girl.

31:26.275 --> 31:27.973
She's already here.

31:30.018 --> 31:34.196
♪

31:34.240 --> 31:36.503
- Kayla's inside the warehouse.
Hit it now.

31:36.546 --> 31:38.809
- On it.

31:38.853 --> 31:42.117
[dramatic music]

31:42.161 --> 31:43.162
- Stack.

31:43.205 --> 31:44.728
- Tight, tight, tight.

31:44.772 --> 31:49.995
♪

31:50.038 --> 31:51.779
- Do it, Jess.

31:53.389 --> 31:55.391
♪

31:55.435 --> 31:56.610
Do it now.

31:58.960 --> 32:04.618
♪

32:07.534 --> 32:08.752
Do it.

32:12.017 --> 32:15.846
♪

32:19.111 --> 32:22.941
[laughter]

32:25.856 --> 32:27.684
[laughter continues]

32:27.728 --> 32:30.383
- Stand down. Stand down now.
It was a test.

32:36.084 --> 32:37.694
[laughter]

32:40.045 --> 32:42.003
- Can't believe
you was gonna kill me, Jess.

32:44.005 --> 32:45.354
Thought we were friends.

32:45.398 --> 32:47.835
- I love you, Kayla, but...

32:47.878 --> 32:49.489
the gang comes first.

32:49.532 --> 32:51.099
- Told you she was down.

32:51.143 --> 32:53.667
All that BS with teacher
had nothing to do with Jess.

32:53.710 --> 32:54.929
It was all him.

32:54.973 --> 32:56.496
Miller.

32:56.539 --> 32:57.584
- Wait.

32:57.627 --> 33:00.500
So you--
you thought that was me.

33:00.543 --> 33:02.632
That I wanted out?

33:02.676 --> 33:04.504
- Started hearing things, Jess.

33:04.547 --> 33:05.896
Lucky for you,
Kayla had your back.

33:05.940 --> 33:07.159
Said you were loyal.

33:07.202 --> 33:09.161
The rest of us
just wanted to make sure.

33:10.989 --> 33:13.078
- No, it's not my fault

33:13.121 --> 33:15.863
my teacher was some type
of do-gooder, you know?

33:15.906 --> 33:18.692
I kept telling him to leave
my ass alone, but he wouldn't.

33:18.735 --> 33:20.433
You know,
kept trying to help me.

33:20.476 --> 33:21.521
- I know.

33:23.262 --> 33:24.828
That's why we killed him.

33:28.615 --> 33:30.356
- We got him.
Hit the warehouse now.

33:30.399 --> 33:32.053
[suspenseful music]

33:32.097 --> 33:33.228
- [grunts]

33:33.272 --> 33:34.621
FBI!

33:34.664 --> 33:36.536
On the ground!
Show me your hands!

33:36.579 --> 33:38.320
- FBI, get on the ground!

33:38.364 --> 33:39.626
- Drop the weapon!

33:41.323 --> 33:44.022
- Come on, down, down, down!
We got a runner!

33:44.065 --> 33:46.372
- Did you not hear me?
- I said get down.

33:46.415 --> 33:49.201
- [grunts]

33:49.244 --> 33:51.072
- Do you not hear me?

33:51.116 --> 33:52.682
- Back stacks are clear!

33:52.726 --> 33:54.206
♪

33:54.249 --> 33:55.424
- Marco Gomez,
you are under arrest

33:55.468 --> 33:57.035
for the murder
of Patrick Miller.

33:59.950 --> 34:02.605
♪

34:02.649 --> 34:04.346
- Don't worry.
This is just for show.

34:06.305 --> 34:07.480
I'm gonna take you
to your home,

34:07.523 --> 34:09.090
you're gonna be able
to pack your things,

34:09.134 --> 34:10.526
say good-bye to your aunt.

34:10.570 --> 34:12.398
We're gonna take you
to an apartment in the city

34:12.441 --> 34:15.096
where you're gonna be safe
until things are official.

34:15.140 --> 34:16.880
- Okay, cool.

34:23.974 --> 34:25.237
- Okay, there's gonna be agents

34:25.280 --> 34:26.803
surrounding your house
the whole time.

34:26.847 --> 34:28.936
There's nothing
to be afraid of.

34:28.979 --> 34:30.329
You did great.

34:36.248 --> 34:38.206
♪

34:38.250 --> 34:40.339
- Make sure everything's clear.

34:46.562 --> 34:50.349
- Jessica did good, though.
Stayed calm, focused.

34:50.392 --> 34:54.570
- Yeah, well, growing up hard
has its advantages.

34:54.614 --> 34:56.094
- Yeah, well, the good news is,

34:56.137 --> 34:58.096
WITSEC can't deny her now,
not after that.

35:00.489 --> 35:02.709
Um, listen, about before,

35:02.752 --> 35:06.365
I had no right to question
what Jessica did in Mexico.

35:06.408 --> 35:10.369
- Well, it wasn't right for me
to question your choice either.

35:10.412 --> 35:11.631
- What do you mean?

35:13.546 --> 35:15.025
- I have no doubt
you'd take the bullet.

35:20.161 --> 35:23.947
♪

35:23.991 --> 35:25.688
OA?

35:31.041 --> 35:33.261
- Murder weapon?
- Sure looks that way.

35:33.305 --> 35:35.089
[phone buzzes]

35:38.397 --> 35:41.139
We gotta go.
We gotta go right now.

35:41.182 --> 35:42.792
- Um, can you get this
to the lab?

35:42.836 --> 35:44.011
- Mm-hmm.

35:46.927 --> 35:48.494
- Hey, what the hell's
going on?

35:48.537 --> 35:50.322
- They got here
five minutes ago.

35:50.365 --> 35:52.324
- Guys, listen, if I may...

35:52.367 --> 35:53.977
- We have
an order of removal.

35:54.021 --> 35:56.502
- Okay, she's working
with us, the FBI.

35:56.545 --> 35:57.938
So just let her go.

35:57.981 --> 35:59.069
- Can't do that.

35:59.113 --> 36:00.767
- Let her go into my custody.

36:00.810 --> 36:02.943
I promise we will work
everything out later.

36:02.986 --> 36:05.032
- Like I said,
we have an order of removal.

36:05.075 --> 36:08.166
- Okay, and like I said,
she's working with the FBI.

36:08.209 --> 36:11.212
- I don't have discretion here.
I'm just executing an order.

36:11.256 --> 36:12.779
So if you want to intervene,
you're gonna have to find

36:12.822 --> 36:14.215
someone way more
important than me.

36:14.259 --> 36:16.478
- No problem--who's your boss?
We'll call right now.

36:16.522 --> 36:18.915
- Doesn't work that way.

36:18.959 --> 36:20.613
- No, no.
You're not taking her anywhere.

36:20.656 --> 36:23.659
- No jurisdiction.
- Hey, hey, don't touch her.

36:23.703 --> 36:25.139
- I'm just doing my job.
- Well, do your job

36:25.183 --> 36:26.575
without putting your hands
on my partner.

36:26.619 --> 36:27.663
Do you understand me?

36:27.707 --> 36:30.100
- Both of you, step back, now.

36:30.144 --> 36:32.015
- I'm not moving.
- Neither am I.

36:32.059 --> 36:33.321
- Then you're gonna
have to shoot me

36:33.365 --> 36:34.888
'cause I'm taking her in.

36:34.931 --> 36:36.498
- No you're not.
- Back off.

36:36.542 --> 36:38.674
- I swear--
get off me!

36:38.718 --> 36:40.241
Jessica, I'm gonna
get you out of there.

36:42.896 --> 36:45.377
- There's nothing we can do.
- Oh, yeah?

36:47.727 --> 36:48.858
Isobel.

36:48.902 --> 36:50.208
I need your help.

36:57.737 --> 36:59.434
- Someone from the Bureau
called yesterday

36:59.478 --> 37:02.959
and asked us to verify
her immigration status.

37:03.003 --> 37:04.657
So we looked into it

37:04.700 --> 37:07.225
and realized
she's a member of the DT 15.

37:07.268 --> 37:09.270
So we issued
an order of removal.

37:09.314 --> 37:11.968
- I understand that,
but she's been working with us.

37:12.012 --> 37:14.232
We're trying to get her
into WITSEC.

37:14.275 --> 37:17.278
- She's a known member
of a violent street gang.

37:17.322 --> 37:19.367
- That she's trying
to get out of.

37:19.411 --> 37:21.804
That's why she came to New York
in the first place.

37:21.848 --> 37:23.893
That's why she was willing
to wear a wire,

37:23.937 --> 37:26.156
so that we could catch
five known gang members.

37:26.200 --> 37:28.158
- She's still a member
of the DT 15s.

37:28.202 --> 37:30.465
Her asylum application
is pending.

37:30.509 --> 37:32.293
That makes her eligible
for deportation.

37:32.337 --> 37:33.816
- So make her ineligible.

37:33.860 --> 37:36.341
- I can't.
- Why not?

37:36.384 --> 37:39.605
- My job is to deport
violent immigrants,

37:39.648 --> 37:41.433
not protect them.

37:43.565 --> 37:46.046
The way things are these days,
I intervene

37:46.089 --> 37:48.527
in a case like this,
I'm a dead man.

37:48.570 --> 37:49.963
- And if you don't,

37:50.006 --> 37:52.792
she's a dead woman, for real.

37:52.835 --> 37:55.360
- I'm sorry.
My hands are tied.

37:57.710 --> 37:59.277
- Hey, did you get my text?

37:59.320 --> 38:01.714
ICE is not playing ball.
- Yeah, but good news.

38:01.757 --> 38:03.281
My friend has agreed
to represent Jessica.

38:03.324 --> 38:04.586
She's already here.

38:04.630 --> 38:06.109
- And already
bossing us around.

38:06.153 --> 38:07.894
So I'm trying to get Mona
to send over a letter

38:07.937 --> 38:09.548
from the U.S. Attorney's office

38:09.591 --> 38:11.376
saying that they're gonna call
Jessica as a material witness

38:11.419 --> 38:12.768
in Miller's murder trial.

38:12.812 --> 38:14.379
- Great, if ICE deports her,
she can't testify,

38:14.422 --> 38:15.554
so a violent killer goes free.

38:15.597 --> 38:17.164
At least that's what
she'll argue.

38:17.207 --> 38:19.079
- I mean, that's great.

38:19.122 --> 38:20.472
I mean, it sounds like
we're off to a hell of a start.

38:20.515 --> 38:21.690
- Well, we are,
but we need more.

38:21.734 --> 38:23.866
We need Jessica's handler,
Agent Bell.

38:23.910 --> 38:25.433
- That's me.
- Okay.

38:25.477 --> 38:27.392
I'm gonna need you to convince
the judge that Jessica

38:27.435 --> 38:30.046
is a significant public benefit
to the United States.

38:30.090 --> 38:32.397
Translation: she's a great kid.

38:32.440 --> 38:34.703
The law is vague in the
definition of "public benefit,"

38:34.747 --> 38:36.357
so just speak from the heart.

38:36.401 --> 38:38.533
Tell the judge what you think
about Jessica

38:38.577 --> 38:40.318
and why she should stay
in this country.

38:40.361 --> 38:42.015
- Okay.
- All right.

38:42.058 --> 38:43.973
Hearing's tomorrow morning.
If I were you, I'd get to work.

38:46.236 --> 38:47.499
If I may, Your Honor,

38:47.542 --> 38:50.328
I'd like to ask
Special Agent Maggie Bell

38:50.371 --> 38:51.372
to address the bench

38:51.416 --> 38:53.418
in the hope
of further establishing

38:53.461 --> 38:57.291
the significant public benefit
Ms. Sanchez can provide.

38:57.335 --> 38:59.119
- That's fine.
Agent Bell, please approach.

39:15.222 --> 39:17.659
- Jessica Sanchez came
to the United States

39:17.703 --> 39:21.359
to escape the violence
and cruelty of the DT 15s--

39:21.402 --> 39:23.752
a gang that she was born into.

39:23.796 --> 39:25.450
Despite her best efforts
to outrun her past,

39:25.493 --> 39:28.409
she was found by the gang
and forced to rejoin.

39:28.453 --> 39:32.370
Desperate, she sought the help
of her teacher, Patrick Miller.

39:32.413 --> 39:34.807
After finding out
the gang leader, Marco Gomez,

39:34.850 --> 39:36.112
and the rest of the crew

39:36.156 --> 39:38.114
took baseball bats and machetes

39:38.158 --> 39:40.813
and brutally beat Patrick
to death,

39:40.856 --> 39:43.816
Jessica blamed herself
for his murder.

39:43.859 --> 39:45.252
But rather than cower,

39:45.295 --> 39:46.775
she agreed to risk her life

39:46.819 --> 39:48.864
and help the FBI arrest
the people responsible

39:48.908 --> 39:50.953
for this heinous crime.

39:50.997 --> 39:52.302
Because of her,

39:52.346 --> 39:54.392
there are fewer violent
criminals on the street,

39:54.435 --> 39:57.177
resulting in fewer assaults
and murders in the future.

39:59.788 --> 40:02.748
[solemn music]

40:02.791 --> 40:08.101
♪

40:08.144 --> 40:10.146
Your Honor,
may I approach the bench?

40:10.190 --> 40:11.409
- You may.

40:16.501 --> 40:17.893
- Your Honor, I know

40:17.937 --> 40:20.461
that this is a legally
complicated situation,

40:20.505 --> 40:22.463
but to me, it's pretty simple.

40:22.507 --> 40:27.816
Jessica Sanchez is an unusually
courageous and honest woman.

40:27.860 --> 40:29.644
And under
incredibly challenging

40:29.688 --> 40:31.516
and dangerous circumstances,

40:31.559 --> 40:33.213
my team and I

40:33.256 --> 40:35.737
watched her continually
put herself in harm's way

40:35.781 --> 40:38.218
for the greater good.

40:38.261 --> 40:42.614
And for the opportunity
to live a better life.

40:42.657 --> 40:45.007
She's the type of person
that we should be

40:45.051 --> 40:46.966
bending over backwards
to keep in this country,

40:47.009 --> 40:49.316
not deport.

40:49.359 --> 40:51.927
I believe we have a duty
to protect her.

40:51.971 --> 40:54.234
We can't just
look the other way

40:54.277 --> 40:56.932
knowing
that if she gets shipped back

40:56.976 --> 41:01.110
to Tampico, Mexico, someone--

41:01.154 --> 41:04.026
someone will take her life.

41:04.070 --> 41:06.246
This is not who we are.

41:06.289 --> 41:09.205
And this is not
what our country is about.

41:10.946 --> 41:12.295
Thank you.

41:18.171 --> 41:21.087
- Thank you, Agent Bell.
That was quite a statement.

41:21.130 --> 41:24.438
And your belief in Ms. Sanchez
is quite apparent.

41:24.482 --> 41:25.961
She is a brave, young woman

41:26.005 --> 41:29.574
who has helped the country
at great risk to herself.

41:34.448 --> 41:36.102
But I am afraid
I have no choice

41:36.145 --> 41:38.452
but to enter
an order of removal.

41:38.496 --> 41:40.933
- Hey, what the hell
are you talking about?

41:40.976 --> 41:42.761
- Sit down,
or I will hold you in content.

41:42.804 --> 41:44.632
- No, Your Honor--
- Sit down now.

41:44.676 --> 41:45.633
- Maggie.

41:47.679 --> 41:49.898
- Whether we like it or not,
the law is clear.

41:49.942 --> 41:53.641
A person with a violent history
cannot apply for asylum.

41:53.685 --> 41:56.905
Even though Ms. Sanchez
cooperated with the FBI,

41:56.949 --> 41:59.255
her affiliation with the DT 15s

41:59.299 --> 42:03.477
